    "Therefore, 208 documents were found, from which 30 were finally selected according to their alignment with the topic of this survey, their publication date and relevance.",
    "bibliography (star: top-10 journal from the above image, blue: Computer Graphics journal, orange: conferences)",
    "There are numerous studies that explain how human vision works by analyzing everything from the eye to the brain processes involved (De Valois and De Valois 1980; Livingstone and Hubel 1988; Wandell 1995; Palmer 1999; Li 2014).",
    "In this section, we are going to focus on eyetracking, how it is performed and why it is useful.",
    "First of all, we must differentiate between the terms \"eye-tracking\" and \"gaze-tracking\", as they are often used interchangeably but denote distinct aspects of visual monitoring."
